{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Exclude HMOs from permitted development rights so residents have their say",
        "additional_details": "HMOs can have a significant impact on local communities, sometimes leading to increased noise, parking issues, and a decrease in the overall quality of life for local residents. By allowing local residents to have a say in the approval process, the government can ensure that the concerns and needs of the community are taken into consideration.",
        "background": "We believe the Government must not let properties be converted to Houses in Multiple Occupation (HMOs) without planning permission, under permitted development rights, to allow residents within the area to have a say in the decision-making process.",
